<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!DOCTYPE paragraph PUBLIC "-//IFRS//DTD DITA Paragraph//EN" "../../../DocTypes/com.ifrs.doctype/dtd/paragraph.dtd"><paragraph base="F16125508" id="IFRS11_27" principles="yes"><paranum class="- topic/title paragraph/paranum "/><titlealts><navtitle>27</navtitle></titlealts><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IFRS 11"/><data name="paranum" value="27"/></prolog><body outputclass="bold"><p id="IFRS11_P0076">In its separate financial statements, a party that participates in, but does not have joint control of, a joint arrangement shall account for its interest in: </p><ol outputclass="static" base="F16125510" id="IFRS11_L0004" type="lower-alpha"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value> <p base="F16125523" id="IFRS11_P0077">a joint operation in accordance with <xref base="F16217380" href="IFRS11_23.dita#IFRS11_23" id="IFRS11_X0122">paragraph 23</xref>;</p></li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value> <p base="F16125526" id="IFRS11_P0078">a joint venture in accordance with <xref base="F68073777" href="../ifrs09/IFRS09_TOC.dita#IFRS09_TOC0001" id="IFRS11_X0123">IFRS 9</xref>, unless the entity has significant influence over the joint venture, in which case it shall apply <xref base="F16217399" href="../ias27/IAS27_10.dita#IAS27_10" id="IFRS11_X0124">paragraph 10 of IAS 27</xref> (as amended in 2011).</p></li></ol></body></paragraph>